%I A309410 #26 Jun 12 2026 14:58:48
%S A309410 17,691,113749,389089
%N A309410 Numbers k such that (41^k + 1)/42 is prime.
%C A309410 Larger terms correspond to probable primes.
%H A309410 P. Bourdelais, <a href="https://listserv.nodak.edu/cgi-bin/wa.exe?A2=NMBRTHRY;417ab0d6.0906">A Generalized Repunit Conjecture</a>.
%H A309410 OEIS Wiki, <a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/Primes_of_the_form_(a%5En%2Bb%5En)/(a%2Bb)_and_(a%5En-b%5En)/(a-b)">Primes of the form (a^n+b^n)/(a+b) and (a^n-b^n)/(a-b)</a>.
%t A309410 Do[p=Prime[n]; If[ PrimeQ[(41^p + 1)/42], Print[p]], {n, 1, 1000000}]
%o A309410 (PARI) is(n)=ispseudoprime((41^n+1)/42)
%K A309410 nonn,hard,more
%O A309410 1,1
%A A309410 _Paul Bourdelais_, Jul 29 2019
%E A309410 a(4) from _Paul Bourdelais_, Jun 12 2026
